<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 7:54AM CDT  by NWS San Angelo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Haskell, northeastern Jones, northwestern Shackelford and southern
Throckmorton Counties through 845 AM CDT...
At 753 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Avoca, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Stamford, Throckmorton, Lake Stamford Marina, The Intersection Of Us-
183 And Us-283 and The Intersection Of Us-380 And Highway 222.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
